overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, providing a detailed specification and an existing
  Statement of Work. The agent performed a thorough analysis, identifying
  several missing features and gaps in the current implementation, which were
  then prioritized into a detailed action plan. Following this, the agent
  proceeded to implement the first three high-priority items: a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness interference with associated safety warnings, explicit
  detection and reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea), and
  the logic for identifying and reporting Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. These
  changes involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components, and
  report generation logic for both web and PDF outputs."
